# verylegit-marketplace plugin rules

A Claude Code plugin marketplace. See [AGENTS.md](mdc:AGENTS.md) for full context.

## Plugin structure

Every plugin lives at `plugins/<name>/` with:

- `.claude-plugin/plugin.json` (required) — must include `name`, `version`, `description`, `author`
- Optional `skills/`, `commands/`, `mcp/`, `hooks/`, `hooks-handlers/` directories, declared in `plugin.json`

## Marketplace registration

When adding a new plugin, you MUST also:

1. Add an entry to [.claude-plugin/marketplace.json](mdc:.claude-plugin/marketplace.json) with `name`, `description`, `source: "./plugins/<name>"`, and `category`.
2. Add a documentation section to [README.md](mdc:README.md) matching the existing format (tagline, description, usage examples, requirements).

A plugin without both of these is invisible to users.

## Skill descriptions are triggers

- Every `SKILL.md` frontmatter `description` field is the trigger signal for Claude Code.
- Vague descriptions cause skills to never activate. Be specific: list trigger phrases, use cases, and explicit cues.
- Match the style of existing skills in this repo (`captain`, `debate`, `bear-notes`).

## MCP servers

- Node.js 18+, ESM (`.mjs`).
- Each plugin's `mcp/` has its own `package.json`. Don't introduce a root-level `node_modules`.
- Stdio transport only unless explicitly asked otherwise.
- Document macOS / system requirements in both README.md and the plugin's SKILL.md.

## Slash commands

- One file per command at `plugins/<name>/commands/<command>.md`.
- File must be self-contained — readable without external context.
- File name MUST match the slash command name.

## No dependencies between plugins

Each plugin in this marketplace is standalone. Don't import code from one plugin into another.

## No telemetry, no bundled binaries

- Never add network analytics, error reporting, or phone-home.
- No compiled binaries committed; source only.
